         <abstract>
            <p>We consider numerical approximations to solutions of systems of hyperbolic conservation laws of the form $\partial u/\partial t + \partial f(u)/\partial x = 0, u \in \mathbf{R}^n$ and $f: R^n \rightarrow R^n$ smooth. We show that conservative three-point second-order accurate methods cannot satisfy a local entropy inequality.</p>
          </abstract>
